1. Create Vnet and then create public subnet for create public subnet dont click on no outbound access and then create public VM and create private VM in public subnet.

2. connect public vm via ssh open cmd in laptop and ssh azureuser@public.Ip 

3. Run conmmdnd wget https://tomcat.apache.org/download-native.cgi

4. connect the private VM --> ssh azureuser@private.ip 

5. Run this command --> wget https://tomcat.apache.org/download-native.cgi

6. It will also downlodad in private VM without Nat gateway beacuse in subnet level we did not enabled no outbound access

7. create private subnet click on no outbound access and then create private VM in private subnet.

8. Connect newly created private VM through public VM of public-subnet

9. Run this command --> wget https://tomcat.apache.org/download-native.cgi

10. It will not download because nat gateway not configured.

11. Search for nat and create nat and click on create -->select resource group give next --> in outbound access select new nat ip then select
    private subnet and review and create.

12. Then check the command --> wget https://tomcat.apache.org/download-native.cgi
